Hundreds of members of the Enlightened Christian Gathering Church gathered outside the Pretoria Specialised Commercial Crimes Court on Friday to support their leader prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, Mary, as they were appearing. The has been transferred to the Gauteng High Court in Pretoria for trial. PAPA'S CASE POSTPONED The couple is facing charges of money-laundering, fraud and contravention of the Prevention of Organised Crime Act (Poca). Their trial was postponed in August for the state and defence to submit representations. 'BUSHIRI OWES ME MONEY!" The members said they drove from different provinces to support their “father”. “You people will never understand what this man of God has sacrificed for us,” they said. PICS & VIDEOS: ROLLING AND PRAYING FOR BUSHIRI! They were chanting songs and some prayed in different languages.  Song, tongues and fire....Hundreds of members of the Enlightened Christian Gathering Church gathered outside the Pretoria Specialised Commercial Crimes Court on Friday to support their leader prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, #Bushiri pic.twitter.com/fpsIgcWAva 